Prodorsum
. Rostrum rounded. Lamellae well separated, protruding in medio-distal part. Translamella thin, distinct. Rostral (
12–14
) and lamellar (
6–8
) setae setiform, thin, smooth. Interlamellar setae (
6–8
) thickened, barbed. Bothridial setae (
69–77
) setiform, thickened, ciliate unilaterally; distal cilia form weakly visible head in some specimens. Exobothridial setae and their alveoli absent. Tutoria (
tu
) long, widely knife-like.

